  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large skillet or wok over medium\u2011high heat.",
    "Season the sliced chicken with salt, pepper, cumin, smoked paprika, chili powder, and ground cinnamon.",
    "Add the chicken to the skillet and cook until browned and cooked through, about 5\u20116 minutes; remove and set aside.",
    "In the same skillet, add the garlic, onion, bell pepper, zucchini, and mushrooms; stir\u2011fry for 4\u20115 minutes until veggies are just tender.",
    "Return the chicken to the skillet and pour in the chicken broth; bring to a simmer.",
    "Stir in lime juice and let the mixture reduce slightly, about 2 minutes.",
    "Remove from heat and fold in the Greek yogurt until the sauce becomes velvety and smooth.",
    "Season again with salt and pepper if needed, then sprinkle chopped cilantro on top before serving."
